name: Honda Tadakatsu (1K Celebrations)
description:
Honda Tadakatsu or also known as Honda Heihachiro is a samurai who served Tokugawa Ieyasu during the civil war (Sengoku Jidai). Born March 17, 1548, Honda Tadakatsu grew up to be a very tough and brutal samurai on the battlefield. It is said that the name Tadakatsu was given by Tokugawa Ieyasu because of his toughness on the battlefield. His most famous feature is the deer antlers mounted on his helmet, these horns aim to ensure he is always easily recognized by opponents who want to challenge him on the battlefield.

Thank you to everyone who has supported me all this time, this object is my thanks to all of you. Thanks.
